===============================================================================

                     Scalingo Database Cloner Installation Complete!

===============================================================================

Configuration file created: config/initializers/scalingo_database_cloner.rb

NEXT STEPS:

1. Edit config/initializers/scalingo_database_cloner.rb:
   - Set your clone_source_scalingo_app_name (the Scalingo app to clone from)  
   - Configure Slack integration: set slack_webhook_url if using Slack notifications
   - Set exclude_tables if needed
   - Configure seeds_file_path if you want to run seeds after cloning

2. Test your configuration:
   bundle exec rake scalingo_database_cloner:test_clone

3. Run database clone:
   bundle exec rake scalingo_database_cloner:clone

4. For automated scheduling, create cron.json at project root:
   {
     "jobs": [
       {
         "command": "0 7 * * 0 bundle exec rake scalingo_database_cloner:clone",
         "size": "2XL"
       }
     ]
   }

For full documentation, visit:
https://github.com/navidemad/scalingo-database-cloner

===============================================================================